Package fr.uge.net.tcp.nonblocking.http

Record HTTPPacket

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
fr.uge.net.tcp.nonblocking.http.HTTPPacket
public record HTTPPacket(HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType type, java.lang.String contentType, java.nio.ByteBuffer content, java.lang.String resource)
extends java.lang.Record
type : type (not null) of the packet that can be either:
  • HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.REQUEST -> in this case every fields are null except resource which is the request.
  • HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.BAD_RESPONSE -> in this case every fields are null except resource.
  • HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.GOOD_RESPONSE -> in this case contentType contains the type of the content and content contains the content of the HTTP response (the buffer is in read-mode) and resource contains the name of the received resource. None of the fields can be null.
